Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potatoes{2} into 2cm wide wedges
(no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer.
Drizzle with @oil{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then
spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%mins}.
Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the stalks, core and seeds. Pop on another
baking tray cut side down. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Roast in your oven until completely softened and slightly charred,
~{20-25%mins}.

Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Pop the @falafel mix{150%g} into a medium
#mixing bowl{} with the lemon zest and @chermoula spice mix{1}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{} and add the @water{150%ml}. Mix together until well
combined then set aside for ~{3-4%mins} (the mixture will thicken in this time)
or until ready to cook.

Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} and set 1 big leaf aside per person
(this is to go on the burger). Separate the rest of the leaves. Halve the
@baby plum tomatoes{125%g} and pop into a medium #bowl{}. Squeeze in the lemon
juice and add the @olive oil{1}. Season with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Set aside.

> You'll add the lettuce later, if you add it now the acid from the lemon juice
> will wilt it.

Once the falafel mixture has thickened, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large
#frying pan{} over medium high heat. Once hot, shape the falafel mixture into
patty shapes with your hands (1 per person) and lay in your pan.

> Wet your hands before shaping the falafels to prevent them from sticking to
> your hands.

Cook until browned, ~{2-3%mins}, then carefully turn and cook until the other
side is browned too, ~{2-3%mins} more. Carefully transfer to the baking tray
with the peppers and bake on the top shelf of your oven until firm and cooked
through, ~{8-10%mins}.

Meanwhile, halve the @glazed burger buns{2}. Pop them in the oven for the last
~{2%mins} of wedge and falafel cooking time. Serve the falafel burgers on the
bottom of the buns with 1 pepper half per person and 1 lettuce leaf per person
on top, followed by the @sweet chilli sauce{32%g}, @mayonnaise{1} and the bun
lid. Add the remaining lettuce leaves to the dressing and toss to combine. Serve
the burger with the salad and sweet potato wedges alongside. Enjoy!